 size=1> I am not new to anime, but tonight was the first night I actually read a graphic novel (manga).  I read Volume 1 of Ranma1/2 in less than an hour!!!  It is sooo funny.  I love Ranma's father who keeps on holding up the signs when turned into a panda.  I also started reading Volume 1 of Dragonball.  It is a lot better than I thought.  I thought it was really funny.  What do you guys think of those 2 mangas? <p>The geek WILL inherit the earth - Collected Sayings of Muad 'Dib</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/9/02 8:15:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> Fans of both. Was collecting the Ranma 1/2 manga, but then it started dissapearing at my comic shop so I stopped. Of course, it's there again... but I have a huge gap and don't feel like buying it again. Seen the anime through the 4th season though.<br>
<br>
Fan of the Dragonball manga also. <p><table width=100% border=0>
<tr>
<td>
Thomas Bonvillain<br>
<img src=http://www.undeadart.com/temp/banner/banner.gif><a href=http://www.undeadart.com>undeadart.com</a>
</td>
<td><a href=http://pkimage.dhs.org/crit/crit.htm>Click here</a> for a broken link!<br><br>
</td>
<tr>
</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upuerumbris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Puer Umbris </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/10/02 2:51:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.yuyuhakusho.com/characters/yusuke.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> I dont have anywhere near enough money to buy the manga books, but last night my parents and I went to Barnes and Noble just to hang out and I read the first Ranma volume in less than an hour.  After I read the first volume I looked around for the second but they didnt have it.  Then I just checked out Dragonball.  At first I thought is was quasi-kiddy stuff before I started reading, but then i saw the 13 up label and decided to give it a go.  I love both of them. <p>The geek WILL inherit the earth - Collected Sayings of Muad 'Dib</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uotakulad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/10/02 8:34:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> My big pet peeve right now is the cost of comics.<br>
<br>
They're digging their own grave. How many kids can drop $5 for one comic (that's what they cost here). I suppose the comics industry has become a victim of its own success. There are more titles than ever, and print runs are low.<br>
<br>
If there was a store that rented graphic novels for say $3, would you rent them? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/10/02 10:51:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> Well, the reason comic prices are rising (most of them) is because of rising paper and printing costs. Todd McFarlane (opinions of the actual comic aside) NEVER changed the price of Spawn from it's $1.95 (US) price tag (except the double sized #50) until just recently, starting with issue 100, to $2.50. He was one of the few (and only one I know of) that actually tried to keep the price steady and kept it low as long as he could.<br>
<br>
But yeah, some just inflate the price for no good reason. I know a LOT of people at image used to do it all the time when the company was still new. Then there's all the special covers and stuff like that raising the price.<br>
<br>
But would I rent a graphic novel for $3? I don't think that'd work out that great. I don't forsee those things being in very good shape for long by renting them out. <p><table width=100% border=0>
<tr>
<td>
Thomas Bonvillain<br>
<img src=http://www.undeadart.com/temp/banner/banner.gif><a href=http://www.undeadart.com>undeadart.com</a>
</td>
<td><a href=http://pkimage.dhs.org/crit/crit.htm>Click here</a> for a broken link!<br><br>
</td>
<tr>
</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usokonosorame.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soko no Sora ME</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/11/02 7:23:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/tenshi_kaze/Ruri_icon.txt WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> I've NO idea how much a comic-length manga costs- I've never seen one in RL o_o;;<br>
<br>
I do know, however, that graphic novels are priced at $29.99 at Chapters, the only place I'm aware of in my city that sells manga. I don't even know if they sell now- last summer I used to go there to read this one shelf full of graphic novels, but I can't seem to find them ever since they rearranged that area <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
