<br>
Then, of course, you can go to Japan and get a weekly comic with about 250 black and white newsprint pages in it, with ten stories by ten authors for a couple bucks. Even the tankouban which collect your favorite series into a compilation volume sells for about $5 for a hundred and fifty pages. <br>
<br>
The difference boils down to a couple main factors, as I see it:  first is the relatively limited circulation, second is the fact that US comics are color, and third that US comics are selling into a &quot;collectors&quot; market.<br>
