I don't know what keeps this country from bringing in Anime/Manga stuff. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udynamiteneon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DynamiteNeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>PK Supporter</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/12/02 11:33:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mangaden.com/pics/junk/b.jpg w=75 l=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> The whole reason I stopped collecting comics was because of the rediculous prices.  One can only take so much of the special glow inthe dark neon cover with 5 variants each costing $5 before you stop having any respect for the companies. <br>
<br>
It might have to do with paper costs, but I also think it had to do with Marvel going public on the stock market.  Once they were on the market, there was outside pressure for them to keep increasing profits every year, so they had to keep increasing or coming up with new ways to make money.<br>
<br>
As for manga, I try to read as much as I can.  There's a lot of translated stuff on the internet if you look for it.  check out <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.noated.com">www.noated.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/12/02 12:25:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First manga experience!</span><hr size=1> I know that's just a cheap ploy to get more money, but that wasn't what I meant. Most of the issues remain at a constant price, unless they're doing a double sized issue or one of those stupid cover deals. Now yeah, they do start going crazy with variants and special covers sometimes, but that's gone down a LOT. I've hardly even seen any lately unless it's for the first issue of something. It's still stupid, but at least they've calmed down on it. My solution is to just not buy all the different covers. I always just buy one. <p><table width=100% border=0>
